00:14:08.653 --> 00:14:11.753
swept for bugs, but it seems that it

00:14:11.763 --> 00:14:14.073
hadn’t been swept that thoroughly.

00:14:14.903 --> 00:14:16.753
There were several secret listening

00:14:16.753 --> 00:14:18.923
devices the Turkish authorities had

00:14:18.923 --> 00:14:20.933
placed inside the consulate that

00:14:20.933 --> 00:14:24.103
the Saudis didn’t find, and they

00:14:24.103 --> 00:14:26.523
recorded everything that happened.

00:14:27.793 --> 00:14:30.093
And I’m sorry to say that this

00:14:30.093 --> 00:14:31.753
is the part where we have to

00:14:31.753 --> 00:14:34.143
go into some grisly detail.

00:14:35.433 --> 00:14:37.783
As Khashoggi was about to arrive,

00:14:38.103 --> 00:14:39.873
one of the agents in charge of the

00:14:39.873 --> 00:14:42.813
operation asked another whether the

00:14:43.203 --> 00:14:46.023
“sacrificial animal” had arrived yet.

00:14:47.550 --> 00:14:49.770
When he did arrive, he was

00:14:49.770 --> 00:14:51.700
taken to an upstairs room,

00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:54.770
and things quickly escalated.

00:14:55.990 --> 00:14:58.750
Khashoggi was told there was an Interpol

00:14:58.780 --> 00:15:01.770
order for his arrest, and he would need

00:15:01.780 --> 00:15:04.190
to be brought back to Saudi Arabia.

00:15:05.326 --> 00:15:07.010
Khashoggi asked if he was being

00:15:07.010 --> 00:15:09.470
kidnapped, then one of the

00:15:09.470 --> 00:15:11.820
agents brought out a syringe.

00:15:12.800 --> 00:15:15.990
Khashoggi's voice became agitated, and he

00:15:15.990 --> 00:15:18.080
asked whether he was going to be drugged.

00:15:19.196 --> 00:15:23.806
This was at 1.33 pm, and it was the last

00:15:23.806 --> 00:15:26.356
thing anyone heard Jamal Khashoggi say.

00:15:27.796 --> 00:15:29.136
It’s thought that he was

00:15:29.136 --> 00:15:31.436
suffocated with a plastic bag.

00:15:32.636 --> 00:15:35.226
And then the forensic surgeon was

00:15:35.226 --> 00:15:38.016
put to work, firing up his bone saw

00:15:38.286 --> 00:15:40.856
and cutting up the body of Saudi

00:15:40.856 --> 00:15:42.776
Arabia’s most famous dissident.

00:15:44.276 --> 00:15:46.196
There are differing opinions as

00:15:46.196 --> 00:15:48.096
to whether Khashoggi was actually

00:15:48.096 --> 00:15:50.236
dead when the dismembering started.

00:15:50.986 --> 00:15:53.296
He was certainly dead when it finished.

00:15:54.396 --> 00:15:57.156
Shortly afterwards, a Saudi agent was

00:15:57.186 --> 00:15:59.616
pictured leaving the consulate, dressed

00:15:59.616 --> 00:16:02.486
up in Khashoggi’s clothes, complete with

00:16:02.486 --> 00:16:05.186
his hat and a fake little goatee beard.

00:16:06.326 --> 00:16:08.736
He went to the famous Blue Mosque,

00:16:09.006 --> 00:16:10.626
before slipping into the bathroom,

00:16:10.986 --> 00:16:12.916
changing back into his own

00:16:12.956 --> 00:16:15.396
clothes and dumping Khashoggi’s.

00:16:16.496 --> 00:16:18.316
As to what happened to Khashoggi’s

00:16:18.326 --> 00:16:20.596
body, there are only a handful

00:16:20.596 --> 00:16:22.216
of people who know the truth.

00:16:23.226 --> 00:16:26.076
Some commentators suggest it was wrapped

00:16:26.086 --> 00:16:28.846
in plastic and taken out of the consulate

00:16:29.026 --> 00:16:32.286
in bags, others that it was dissolved

00:16:32.306 --> 00:16:34.866
in acid in the consulate grounds.

00:16:36.196 --> 00:16:38.853
That very afternoon, when her fiancé

00:16:39.146 --> 00:16:40.736
failed to come out of the consulate,

00:16:40.736 --> 00:16:44.276
Khashoggi’s fiancée, Hatice Cengiz

00:16:44.736 --> 00:16:46.996
immediately called Khashoggi’s Turkish

00:16:47.026 --> 00:16:49.266
journalist friend, pleading for help.

00:16:50.580 --> 00:16:54.360
Fortunately, this friend, Yasin Aktay, was

00:16:54.360 --> 00:16:57.910
an aide to President Erdogan, so he was

00:16:57.930 --> 00:17:00.210
able to get things moving pretty quickly.

00:17:01.340 --> 00:17:03.910
From that moment on, what had

00:17:03.910 --> 00:17:05.610
been a private disappearance

00:17:05.830 --> 00:17:08.310
became an international crisis.

00:17:09.420 --> 00:17:11.800
Within hours, Turkish officials

00:17:12.060 --> 00:17:13.710
were quietly alerted that

00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:15.350
something was badly wrong.

00:17:16.770 --> 00:17:19.890
CCTV footage showed Jamal Khashoggi

00:17:20.180 --> 00:17:22.160
entering the consulate, but

00:17:22.570 --> 00:17:24.140
there was no sign of him leaving.

00:17:25.410 --> 00:17:27.700
And the Turkish police could not

00:17:27.700 --> 00:17:30.240
simply walk in and search the building.

00:17:31.290 --> 00:17:32.780
Under international law,

00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:35.580
consulates are protected spaces,

00:17:35.870 --> 00:17:38.630
and entry requires permission

00:17:38.920 --> 00:17:40.320
from the country that runs them.

00:17:41.740 --> 00:17:45.210
Saudi officials insisted that Khashoggi

00:17:45.210 --> 00:17:48.300
had left of his own accord, and that

00:17:48.300 --> 00:17:50.210
there was nothing to investigate.

00:17:51.660 --> 00:17:53.740
For the first few days, Saudi

00:17:53.740 --> 00:17:57.010
Arabia stuck rigidly to this line.

00:17:57.940 --> 00:18:00.080
They said Khashoggi had completed

00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:02.130
his paperwork and walked out.

00:18:02.960 --> 00:18:04.770
Perhaps he might have gone

00:18:04.810 --> 00:18:06.330
elsewhere in Istanbul.

00:18:06.470 --> 00:18:08.220
Perhaps he had met someone.

00:18:08.600 --> 00:18:11.110
Perhaps he had disappeared voluntarily.

00:18:12.240 --> 00:18:15.000
It was an implausible story, but

00:18:15.290 --> 00:18:17.800
it was repeated again and again

00:18:18.020 --> 00:18:20.540
by Saudi officials, almost as if

00:18:20.550 --> 00:18:22.770
repetition alone might make it true.

00:18:24.120 --> 00:18:26.200
They thought, perhaps perfectly

00:18:26.210 --> 00:18:28.110
reasonably, that nobody would

00:18:28.210 --> 00:18:30.010
ever know what had happened

00:18:30.130 --> 00:18:31.630
in the consulate that day.

00:18:32.540 --> 00:18:34.720
Turkey, meanwhile, chose

00:18:34.740 --> 00:18:36.110
a different strategy.

00:18:37.140 --> 00:18:39.090
Rather than confronting Saudi

00:18:39.090 --> 00:18:41.680
Arabia head on, showing its hand,

00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:44.650
Turkish authorities began to leak

00:18:44.710 --> 00:18:47.780
information, slowly and deliberately.

00:18:48.910 --> 00:18:51.540
First came confirmation that a team

00:18:51.540 --> 00:18:53.750
of Saudi officials had flown into

00:18:53.750 --> 00:18:55.850
Istanbul on the day of the killing.

00:18:56.460 --> 00:18:59.480
Then CCTV images of the men

00:18:59.530 --> 00:19:00.490
arriving at the airport.

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:02.740
Then hotel records.

00:19:02.920 --> 00:19:05.870
Then details of the body double wandering

00:19:05.870 --> 00:19:08.146
through the city dressed as Khashoggi.

00:19:09.170 --> 00:19:11.130
Each leak added another

00:19:11.180 --> 00:19:12.970
crack to the Saudi story.

00:19:14.210 --> 00:19:16.920
Turkey never held a press conference

00:19:17.170 --> 00:19:18.680
to announce it had recordings

00:19:18.680 --> 00:19:20.630
from inside the consulate, nor

00:19:20.890 --> 00:19:22.700
did it ever publicly release them.

00:19:23.820 --> 00:19:27.040
Instead, in mid-October, it allowed

00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:29.650
journalists to report that such recordings

00:19:29.650 --> 00:19:32.950
existed, letting Saudi Arabia realise,

00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:35.740
slowly and painfully, that every

00:19:35.740 --> 00:19:38.490
denial had already been contradicted.

00:19:39.656 --> 00:19:41.246
As the days passed, the

00:19:41.246 --> 00:19:42.856
pressure intensified.

00:19:43.356 --> 00:19:45.506
Journalists, governments, and human

00:19:45.506 --> 00:19:47.816
rights groups demanded answers.

00:19:48.656 --> 00:19:50.896
Business leaders began to pull out

00:19:51.066 --> 00:19:52.996
of Saudi investment conferences.

00:19:53.426 --> 00:19:55.386
Western politicians spoke of

00:19:55.426 --> 00:19:57.806
consequences, even if many

00:19:57.806 --> 00:19:59.716
were careful not to go too far.

00:20:00.966 --> 00:20:03.696
The idea that a man, a public figure,

00:20:04.056 --> 00:20:06.876
could walk into a consulate and simply

00:20:06.876 --> 00:20:10.016
vanish was becoming impossible to ignore.

00:20:11.306 --> 00:20:13.446
After more than two weeks of denial,

00:20:13.896 --> 00:20:16.736
Saudi Arabia finally changed its story.

00:20:17.966 --> 00:20:20.616
On the 20th of October, it admitted

00:20:20.856 --> 00:20:22.806
that Jamal Khashoggi was dead.

00:20:23.906 --> 00:20:26.126
But the explanation it offered

00:20:26.506 --> 00:20:28.286
only raised more questions.

00:20:29.696 --> 00:20:31.746
According to the new version,

00:20:32.196 --> 00:20:34.716
Khashoggi had died during a rogue

00:20:34.756 --> 00:20:36.896
interrogation that had gone wrong.

00:20:37.826 --> 00:20:40.196
The operatives involved, Saudi Arabia

00:20:40.196 --> 00:20:43.216
said, had acted without authorisation.

00:20:44.016 --> 00:20:46.016
Several officials were arrested.

00:20:46.396 --> 00:20:48.426
Senior figures were dismissed.

00:20:49.156 --> 00:20:50.686
The Crown Prince, it was

00:20:50.686 --> 00:20:53.236
stressed, knew nothing about it.

00:20:54.446 --> 00:20:56.276
Few people outside the

00:20:56.276 --> 00:20:57.486
kingdom believed it.

00:20:58.866 --> 00:21:01.466
A spontaneous interrogation doesn’t

00:21:01.476 --> 00:21:03.756
normally involve two private jets,

00:21:03.836 --> 00:21:06.676
a 15-man team, a forensic surgeon,

00:21:06.936 --> 00:21:08.916
and a carefully planned cover story.

00:21:10.316 --> 00:21:12.336
Intelligence agencies around the world

00:21:12.616 --> 00:21:15.546
came to the same conclusion: this

00:21:15.986 --> 00:21:18.046
was not an accident; it was a planned

00:21:18.046 --> 00:21:20.946
killing, sponsored by none other than

00:21:20.946 --> 00:21:23.376
the Crown Prince, Mohammed Bin Salman.

00:21:24.693 --> 00:21:25.943
In the months that followed,

00:21:26.213 --> 00:21:27.433
the fallout continued.

00:21:28.660 --> 00:21:30.830
The CIA concluded that Mohammed

00:21:30.830 --> 00:21:33.350
Bin Salman had almost certainly

00:21:33.540 --> 00:21:34.910
approved the operation.

00:21:35.870 --> 00:21:38.700
A United Nations investigator described

00:21:38.700 --> 00:21:41.420
the murder as an extrajudicial killing

00:21:41.720 --> 00:21:44.420
for which the Saudi state was responsible.

00:21:46.270 --> 00:21:49.540
In response, Saudi Arabia held secret

00:21:49.540 --> 00:21:51.780
trials, sentencing some of the men

00:21:51.780 --> 00:21:54.480
involved to prison, while sparing others

00:21:54.660 --> 00:21:56.770
who were closer to the centres of power.

00:21:58.050 --> 00:21:59.830
The proceedings were widely

00:21:59.830 --> 00:22:01.880
dismissed as a whitewash.

00:22:03.220 --> 00:22:06.940
And then, gradually, the world…moved on.

00:22:07.800 --> 00:22:10.720
Strategic interests reasserted themselves.

00:22:11.100 --> 00:22:12.770
Arms deals resumed.

00:22:13.100 --> 00:22:14.740
Diplomacy softened.

00:22:15.750 --> 00:22:18.340
The United States, under President Trump,

00:22:18.760 --> 00:22:21.350
showed no real interest in weighing in.

00:22:22.170 --> 00:22:23.770
Global leaders who had once

00:22:23.780 --> 00:22:26.310
spoken of pariah status were

00:22:26.310 --> 00:22:28.110
photographed shaking hands again.

00:22:28.810 --> 00:22:31.423
A few years later, the same CEOs

00:22:31.476 --> 00:22:33.630
were back in Riyadh, competing

00:22:33.790 --> 00:22:35.700
for lucrative NEOM contracts.

00:22:36.370 --> 00:22:39.150
Even Turkey, after years of tension,

00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:41.550
eventually transferred the remaining

00:22:41.560 --> 00:22:43.690
legal proceedings to Saudi Arabia,

00:22:44.150 --> 00:22:46.090
effectively closing the case.

00:22:47.410 --> 00:22:48.740
Jamal Khashoggi’s body

00:22:49.100 --> 00:22:50.150
was never recovered.

00:22:51.060 --> 00:22:53.170
His fiancée never received the

00:22:53.170 --> 00:22:55.570
documents he went to collect that day.

00:22:56.610 --> 00:22:58.920
And the message sent by his killing

00:22:59.200 --> 00:23:01.840
lingered long after the headlines faded.

00:23:02.420 --> 00:23:03.690
A warning to critics.

00:23:04.000 --> 00:23:05.570
A demonstration of power.

00:23:06.580 --> 00:23:09.380
A reminder that, in the new Saudi Arabia,

00:23:09.720 --> 00:23:12.690
there were limits to reform, and crossing

00:23:12.690 --> 00:23:16.520
them could be fatal: Jamal Khashoggi went

00:23:16.570 --> 00:23:18.750
to his consulate to collect a document.

00:23:19.556 --> 00:23:22.570
What he exposed instead was the true

00:23:22.570 --> 00:23:25.690
cost of dissent in the new Saudi Arabia.

00:23:28.220 --> 00:23:30.790
OK, then, that is it for today's episode

00:23:31.010 --> 00:23:32.760
on the murder of Jamal Khashoggi,

00:23:33.060 --> 00:23:35.020
and with that comes an end to this

00:23:35.040 --> 00:23:37.725
three-part mini-series on MBS and

00:23:37.725 --> 00:23:39.820
the making of modern Saudi Arabia.

00:23:40.380 --> 00:23:41.580
I hope it's been an interesting one

00:23:41.850 --> 00:23:43.330
and that you've learnt something new.

00:23:43.830 --> 00:23:45.480
As always, I would love to know

00:23:45.480 --> 00:23:46.870
what you thought of this episode.

00:23:47.270 --> 00:23:49.260
Saudi Arabia is an increasingly

00:23:49.300 --> 00:23:51.570
popular country for this show, so

00:23:51.880 --> 00:23:53.940
to the wonderful Saudi listeners, I

00:23:53.940 --> 00:23:55.770
would especially like to know what

00:23:55.770 --> 00:23:57.140
you thought about this episode,

00:23:57.350 --> 00:23:59.400
and of this mini-series in general.

00:23:59.780 --> 00:24:01.910
What would you like people to know about

00:24:01.910 --> 00:24:04.680
your country, what changes have you seen

00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:06.920
in your day-to-day lives, and what are

00:24:06.920 --> 00:24:09.110
your hopes and dreams for the future?

00:24:09.680 --> 00:24:11.810
The place for that is our community forum,

00:24:12.050 --> 00:24:14.860
which is at community.leonardoenglish.com.

